1
00:01:28,940 --> 00:01:35,580
Winter Begonia

2
00:01:35,660 --> 00:01:37,979
Episode 7

3
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:42,520
Mr. Cheng,

4
00:01:42,960 --> 00:01:44,840
this used to be the temple built by the eunuchs.

5
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:47,240
It's deserted

6
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:48,360
as no one cares later.

7
00:01:49,160 --> 00:01:51,039
Now there are only a few old eunuchs keeping it.

8
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:04,720
Mr. Cheng,

9
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,080
I want to build a theater here

10
00:02:07,520 --> 00:02:10,120
and sing whatever I want in the future.

11
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:12,080
I don’t have to care about anyone’s feeling,

12
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:13,560
and no one can discipline me.

13
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:16,640
I don’t have to share the earnings with the theater.

14
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:18,160
So I can get the net earnings.

15
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,960
You asked me to come and see the plot.

16
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:23,079
Do you want me to invest?

17
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,400
How could that be?

18
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:26,600
I have an inherited fortune,

19
00:02:26,760 --> 00:02:28,360
but I can't use unless emergency occurs.

20
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:31,600
It's time to spend a lot of money.

21
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:35,360
Alright.

22
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:39,720
Then please leave me a box.

23
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:44,480
I’ll leave the best one to you.

24
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:47,320
That's a deal.

25
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:49,960
-Please give me some money!
-Please give me some money!

26
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:52,160
Pity us!

27
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:54,520
-Please help me!
-Please give me some money!

28
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:56,650
-Please give me some money!
-Pity us!

29
00:02:57,160 --> 00:02:58,600
Please give me some money!

30
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:01,600
Mr. Shang, Mr. Shang!

31
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:04,080
Please give me some money! Mr. Shang!

32
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,200
What are the rules here?

33
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:06,280
Want big money?

34
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:07,520
Sing a new song.

35
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,040
Let me sing first.

36
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:12,120
“I’m a beggar lives in Beitian Temple,

37
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:14,360
belongs to the sect of Liu Jiu'er.”

38
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,080
Biography of Li Wa?

39
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:15,600
I’ve heard it.

40
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:16,960
Listen to me. Listen to me.

41
00:03:17,079 --> 00:03:19,760
“The Chu and Han people are disturbed.

42
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:24,760
Two wise men, Liu Cheng and Yuan Zhao emerged from Dacheng County.

43
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:25,600
That year…”

44
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:26,720
Two Gods Picking Medicine?

45
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,079
Is there anything new?

46
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:29,760
Is there any more?

47
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:30,840
I’m leaving if not.

48
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:32,960
Don't go.

49
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:33,760
Don't drag me.

50
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:34,400
It’s useless.

51
00:03:34,440 --> 00:03:35,120
Go find Mr. Cheng.

52
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:35,880
Mr. Cheng is rich.

53
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:37,760
Mr. Cheng! Mr. Cheng!

54
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:38,360
You poor children,

55
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,240
don't come over!

56
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,480
I might hit you.

57
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:42,200
Drive them away!

58
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:43,880
Don't let them come over to me!

59
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:45,079
Get away!

60
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:46,760
I don't run, I don't run.

61
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:48,040
Don't touch this.

62
00:03:48,079 --> 00:03:48,720
Don't touch this.

63
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:50,560
Don't touch my ring,

64
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,160
and the chain.

65
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:52,880
Alright, alright.

66
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:53,760
come back.

67
00:03:53,760 --> 00:03:54,600
I will give you an IOU.

68
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:55,200
Don’t touch.

69
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:56,760
Don’t touch that!

70
00:03:57,880 --> 00:03:58,920
There is no paper.

71
00:03:59,000 --> 00:03:59,880
It doesn’t matter.

72
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,400
Look at me.

73
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,120
Don’t touch!

74
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:03,880
Don’t touch that!

75
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:04,880
Step aside!

76
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,040
Walk away!

77
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:13,200
Here.

78
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:14,000
Write it on the back.

79
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:16,200
Do you have a pen?

80
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:17,200
Wait a second.

81
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:18,720
Pen, pen.

82
00:04:20,279 --> 00:04:21,399
Give me! Give me that!

83
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:24,000
Give me! Give me that!

84
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:25,080
Mr. Cheng!

85
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:26,520
Bow down.

86
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:27,280
Okay.

87
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:33,320
I owe…

88
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:34,080
What's your name?

89
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:35,280
My name is Er Sha.

90
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:37,560
Er means two.

91
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:41,040
I owe Er…

92
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:42,640
You can’t take the chain.

93
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:45,920
This is too dangerous.

94
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:46,880
Don’t take it.

95
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:47,520
Don’t take it.

96
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:48,960
Mr. Cheng, how to write Sha?

97
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:49,920
I don’t know.

98
00:04:50,159 --> 00:04:50,760
Figure it by yourself.

99
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:54,880
Mr. Cheng, Mr. Cheng. Mr. Cheng.

100
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:56,159
Okay now.

101
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:57,720
Look.

102
00:04:57,960 --> 00:04:58,720
I owe Er...

103
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:00,320
A circle

104
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:01,240
still counts.

105
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:03,240
I owe Er Sha a silver dollar today.

106
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:04,880
Do you know where is Shuiyun Theater?

107
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:05,560
Yes.

108
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:06,040
Go.

109
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:08,160
Okay. Let’s go.

110
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,040
Let’s go to Shuiyun Theater.

111
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:10,600
Let’s go.

112
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:12,600
We have money now.

113
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:16,760
Mr. Cheng, your pen.

114
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:22,840
Mr. Shang.

115
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:23,560
Why are you leaving?

116
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:25,680
Mr. Shang, Mr. Shang, Mr. Shang,

117
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:26,560
don't be like this.

118
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:29,240
Don't leave upon seeing me.

119
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:32,120
It’s a wired day.

120
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:33,480
Uncle,

121
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,400
let's talk.

122
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:37,360
Sir,

123
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:38,680
I’m poor-sighted and

124
00:05:39,159 --> 00:05:40,320
didn't see you.

125
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:43,480
You are full of spirits,

126
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:44,560
with a rounded and undefiled

127
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:45,920
forehead.

128
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:48,360
You must be a master of making money.

129
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:49,360
Excuse me,

130
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:50,400
what do you do?

131
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:51,120
We’ll go first

132
00:05:51,159 --> 00:05:52,440
if you don’t have anything else.

133
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:54,880
Mr. Shang, Mr. Shang, Mr. Shang,

134
00:05:55,159 --> 00:05:56,200
listen to me.

135
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:58,080
I’m not taking your money

136
00:05:58,240 --> 00:06:00,080
for free.

137
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,880
Don't you want to hear something new?

138
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:02,720
I have a new one for you

139
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:03,800
today.

140
00:06:04,720 --> 00:06:05,680
Sing it.

141
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:17,440
“Invite Eight Immortals to the Sacred Hall again.

142
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:19,640
Eight Immortals drifting across the waves.

143
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:21,320
The first immortal is Tieguai Li.

144
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:23,800
Tieguai Li is really strange,

145
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:25,720
with left leg being high and the right leg being low.

146
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:28,120
There are magic spells in the gourd.”

147
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,280
Is this a new song?

148
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,880
This is older than my father.

149
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:34,800
I still have one.

150
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:36,040
Listen to this one.

151
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:40,480
“From the south

152
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:42,280
to the north,

153
00:06:42,320 --> 00:06:44,240
A Lei emerged from Beijing.

154
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:46,200
The table he builds will stretch its legs.

155
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:48,080
The house he builds will not get dusty.”

156
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:51,320
Interesting.

157
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:52,120
Carry on.

158
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:56,760
“Lei is really something.

159
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,520
He can carve beams and paint walls.

160
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:00,360
No nails, no hammers.

161
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:02,360
All he uses are woods.”

162
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:05,160
So hyperbolic!

163
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:06,400
You must be making it up.

164
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:08,040
Look,

165
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:09,920
how could I make it up?

166
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:12,760
A Lei is really living here.

167
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:15,280
It’s on the south end of our street.

168
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:16,880
Mr. Shang,

169
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:18,600
I’ve already sung for you.

170
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:19,360
So…

171
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:22,200
You should…

172
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:25,800
Just this?

173
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:27,240
Please give me more.

174
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:28,000
Too little?

175
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,040
I will give no more.

176
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:31,120
Please help me.

177
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:33,440
I haven't eaten all day.

178
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:35,120
You have a heart of gold.

179
00:07:35,159 --> 00:07:37,360
You have helped so many actors.

180
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:38,840
It won’t bother you to help one more.

181
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:39,800
Don't flatter me.

182
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:41,360
I’m heartless.

183
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:42,520
Let's say this time,

184
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:44,080
I will definitely not give you more money.

185
00:07:45,159 --> 00:07:47,000
If you have no money for me,

186
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:49,400
I don’t have means to earn a living.

187
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:51,200
You have no way to live? I have no money.

188
00:07:51,520 --> 00:07:52,920
OK, fine.

189
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:54,680
I can see.

190
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:56,040
You two

191
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:57,240
are old acquaintance.

192
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,520
Mr. Shang,

193
00:07:58,680 --> 00:08:00,280
let's take it for respecting the elderly.

194
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:02,040
You have a good heart.

195
00:08:02,280 --> 00:08:03,280
I can tell

196
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:05,640
you are a good person.

197
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:07,120
I

198
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:09,600
have seen so many people here.

199
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:11,040
I can see charity and morality

200
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:13,280
in your eyebrows.

201
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:14,680
In the future, you will…

202
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:17,600
-…turn calamities into blessings.
-No!

203
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:18,920
And you’ll have more children and happiness.

204
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:19,880
Let me

205
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:20,520
tell you.

206
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,120
You definitely

207
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,640
can make a fortune.

208
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:28,720
Isn't this robbing money?

209
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:30,760
Look,

210
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:33,280
he’ll use that money for prostitution or gambling.

211
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:34,559
He will use it up before tomorrow.

212
00:08:37,640 --> 00:08:38,440
Forget it.

213
00:08:39,280 --> 00:08:40,480
It's not big money.

214
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:42,120
Don’t be angry with him.

215
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:44,320
It’s not about money.

216
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:46,560
I used to hire him at Shuiyun Theater to run some errands.

217
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:47,600
Guess what?

218
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:50,640
He egged the children into prostitution and gambling.

219
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:51,880
I would definitely send him to the police station

220
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:53,080
if it weren't for his age.

221
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:57,720
What are you looking at?

222
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:00,760
You’re sympathetic,

223
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:03,000
not so heartless.

224
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:04,200
Leader!

225
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:05,280
Leader!

226
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:06,520
Leader!

227
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:07,960
What happened?

228
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:09,960
They’re fighting

229
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:11,880
at home.

230
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:13,560
Someone might be killed.

231
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:15,240
Please come back and take a look!

232
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:17,240
Get out the way!

233
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:18,000
Get out the way!

234
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,400
-What are you doing?
- Get out the way!

235
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:20,560
Put it down, La Yuehong!

236
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,120
Leader is here!

237
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:23,680
Put it down!

238
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:26,120
What happened?

239
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:27,160
-La Yuehong!
-Put down the broadsword!

240
00:09:27,280 --> 00:09:27,960
Leader is here!

241
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,200
Put down the broadsword immediately!

242
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:30,640
Don’t be so disrespectful!

243
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:34,440
What are you doing?

244
00:09:40,160 --> 00:09:41,000
Want a rebellion?

245
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:48,920
Shijiu,

246
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:49,920
tell us.

247
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,520
A while ago,

248
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,800
we saw Liuyue hooked up with

249
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:54,360
Xue Qianshan,

250
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:55,320
the owner of Beiping Newspaper.

251
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:56,560
She denied when I asked her.

252
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:58,240
The Xue family's wedding gifts are delivered today.

253
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:00,000
Why are you fighting

254
00:10:00,680 --> 00:10:02,080
like this

255
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:03,600
just for wedding gifts?

256
00:10:04,400 --> 00:10:04,920
No.

257
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:11,080
Don’t marry him.

258
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:12,000
Stay here.

259
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:13,560
I’ll protect you.

260
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:19,360
The leader asks you to stay.

261
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:20,520
Can you grow up?

262
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:22,120
Moreover,

263
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:24,000
you signed life-long contract with Shuiyun Theater.

264
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:25,560
If leader does not let you go,

265
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:27,280
Xue family can't come here to grab you.

266
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:33,120
Let me tell you,

267
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,200
every girl at Shuiyun Theater,

268
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:37,480
who marries

269
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:39,800
as a concubine,

270
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:42,000
feels regretful.

271
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:46,160
Just for men’s hollow promise,

272
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,920
they sacrifice

273
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,000
all they have learnt

274
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:50,840
for years.

275
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:51,560
Is it worthwhile?

276
00:10:54,760 --> 00:10:55,800
Xue Qianshan

277
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:56,880
said

278
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:58,400
his wives at home

279
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:01,400
are equal-footed

280
00:11:02,040 --> 00:11:03,160
without hierarchy.

281
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:03,840
So silly!

282
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:05,240
Before getting married,

283
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:06,640
men can say anything nice.

284
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:07,880
You’re just an opera actress.

285
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:09,080
You're going to be a doormat

286
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:10,440
if you marry as a concubine.

287
00:11:12,760 --> 00:11:13,120
It’s

288
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:15,560
already

289
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:18,600
too late.

290
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:24,960
Why do you think so?

291
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,840
